   **`flushAtomicCallbacks` implementation** (lines 763-817 of Store.js):
   ```javascript
   flushAtomicCallbacks(isMergingRemoteChanges) {
     let updateDepth = 0;
     while (this.pendingAfterEvents) {
       const events = this.pendingAfterEvents;
       this.pendingAfterEvents = null;
       if (!this.sideEffects.isEnabled()) continue;
       updateDepth++;
       if (updateDepth > 100) {
         throw new Error("Maximum store update depth exceeded, bailing out");
       }
       for (const { before, after } of events.values()) {
         if (before && after && before !== after && !isEqual(before, after)) {
           this.sideEffects.handleAfterChange(before, after, source);
         }
         // ...
       }
     }
   }
   ```

   **`store.atomic` implementation** (lines ~840 of Store.js):
   ```javascript
   atomic(fn, runCallbacks = true, isMergingRemoteChanges = false) {
     return transact(() => {
       if (this._isInAtomicOp) {
         if (!this.pendingAfterEvents) this.pendingAfterEvents = new Map();
         // nested: just run fn
         return fn();
       }
       this._isInAtomicOp = true;
       this.pendingAfterEvents = new Map();
       try {
         const result = fn();
         this.flushAtomicCallbacks(isMergingRemoteChanges);
         return result;
       } finally {
         this.pendingAfterEvents = null;
         this._isInAtomicOp = false;
       }
     });
   }
   ```

   The cascade: `isPropagating = false` is reset in the `finally` block of each handler call within the `for` loop. The `while` loop then picks up newly-added `pendingAfterEvents` (from shapeB's move). In the next iteration, `isPropagating = false` again → shapeB's handler fires → moves shapeA and pin again → infinite loop.

   **Needed fix to `src/tools/pin/use-pin-attachment.ts`** — replace `isPropagating: boolean` with `propagatedIds: Set<TLShapeId>`:
   ```typescript
   // Replace:
   let isPropagating = false

   // With:
   let isPropagating = false
   const propagatedIds = new Set<TLShapeId>()

   // In handler, add guard:
   if (propagatedIds.has(next.id)) {
     propagatedIds.delete(next.id)
     return
   }

   // Before moving shapes:
   for (const update of updates) {
     propagatedIds.add(update.id)
   }
   isPropagating = true
   try {
     editor.run(() => editor.updateShapes(updates.map(...)))
   } finally {
     isPropagating = false
   }
   ```

9. Optional Next Step:
   Fix the cascade bug in `src/tools/pin/use-pin-attachment.ts` by adding a `Set<TLShapeId>` propagation guard. The conversation was working on pin-attach.spec.ts error:

   > "Error: page.evaluate: Error: Maximum store update depth exceeded, bailing out"
   > at `tests/e2e/pin-attach.spec.ts:44:14`

   The fix is to replace the `isPropagating` boolean in `use-pin-attachment.ts` with a `Set<TLShapeId>` that tracks shapes moved by propagation. When shapeB's `afterChange` fires in the next `flushAtomicCallbacks` iteration, the set check skips it (preventing the cascade). Then re-run `pnpm test` and `pnpm test:e2e` to verify all tests pass, then proceed to commit/push/PR.

